universum.studios.android.intent

Class WebIntent

  • java.lang.Object
    • universum.studios.android.intent.BaseIntent<WebIntent>
      • universum.studios.android.intent.WebIntent

  • public class WebIntent
extends BaseIntent<WebIntent>
    A BaseIntent builder implementation providing API for building and starting of intents targeting a web content related applications.

    This intent builder requires only a web Url to be specified via url(String).

    Valid Url for the web intent must comply with Patterns.WEB_URL matcher.

    Author:
    Martin Albedinsky

      • url

        public WebIntent url(String url)
        Sets an URL that should be loaded into framework's web browser. Note, that the specified url must be valid web URL otherwise will be not accepted.

        If the given url is valid, but doesn't contain HTTP or HTTPS prefix, then the HTTP (http://) prefix will be attached to it.

        Parameters:
        url - The desired URL to load into web browser.
        Returns:
        This intent builder to allow methods chaining.
        See Also:
        url()

      • url

        Returns the web URL to be loaded into web browser.
        Returns:
        Valid URL or empty string if not specified yet.

        url(String)

      • ensureCanBuildOrThrow

        protected void ensureCanBuildOrThrow()
        Description copied from class: BaseIntent
        Called to ensure that this builder can build its Intent from its current data.

        If there are some required data missing/not specified, an exception indicating such state should be thrown. The default exception may be created via BaseIntent.cannotBuildIntentException(String).
